<p itemprop="description">A lead infrastructure operations engineer provides strategic leadership for all infrastructure operations activities across the organisation. They establish enterprise-wide operational standards and ensure optimal performance of critical infrastructure systems.</p>

<section class="role-details">
    <h2>Typical responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Provide strategic leadership for infrastructure operations across the organisation</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Establish enterprise-wide operational standards and frameworks</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Drive innovation in infrastructure operations and site reliability engineering</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Lead cross-functional initiatives to improve system reliability and performance</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Represent operations interests in senior leadership forums</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Develop strategic operational partnerships and vendor relationships</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Ensure alignment between operational activities and business objectives</li>
    </ul>
</section>

